        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Congregation House of Israel&#44;<lb/>
                &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/>
                SIMON EZEKIEL&#44; Secretary<lb/></p>
            <p>OFFICE&#44; 637 NORTH SEVENTH ST.					Philadelphia&#44; Decbr 7 1879<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Rev Dr M Elkin<lb/>
                Rev Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>annexed please find copy<lb/> of a communication received by the Board of Managers of the Congregation<lb/> House of Israel.  At a meeting held this day it was<lb/> resolved to refer the same to you for the purpose of having<lb/> the question therein contained&#44; bring before the Board of Rabbis&#44; of<lb/> which <hi rend="underline">you</hi> are a member&#44; and they shall decide&#44; according<lb/> our Jewish rites&#44; <sic>wether</sic> the Board of managers <hi rend="underline">may</hi> grant<lb/> the request <hi rend="underline">or not</hi> please let us know the result as soon<lb/> as practicable.  Yours truly<lb/></p>
            <p>Simon Ezekiel<lb/>
                						Secty<lb/></p>
            <p><hi rend="underline">Copy</hi></p>
            <p>Philada Nov 16. 1879. 902 Walnut St<lb/></p>
            <p>to President and Board of Trustees of Cong. &#34;House of Israel&#44;&#34;¬ù Gentlemen<lb/> desiring to purchase a lot in Mt. Sinai Cemetery and wishing my<lb/> husband the late Julius Davidson buried in this lot&#44; I earnestly<lb/> beg permission&#44; of your honorable Board to have the remains removed<lb/> to said cemetery&#44; praying &#38; hoping that this&#44; my prayer will be<lb/> granted I remain Gentlemen very Respectfully<lb/></p>
            <p>signed R Davidson<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>The President Mr S Nathan has also made application<lb/> to have the remains of his late mother removed<lb/> to Mount Sinai Cemetery<lb/>
                S. E.<lb/></p>
                
              
            <p>Mr Simon Ezekiel<lb/></p>
            <p>Philadelphia December 17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1879<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>The question which the congregation&#44; whose secretary you<lb/> are&#44; submitted to the Board of Hebrew Ministers was discussed at a meeting<lb/> held this morning.<lb/></p>
            <p>I am instructed to reply that the Board feels unauthorized to sanction<lb/> a departure from Rabbinical laws.  According to the latter&#44; the <del>removal</del> disinterment<lb/> of a dead body&#44; as contemplated in the two cases which your communication<lb/> presented&#44; is disallowed.<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours respectfully<lb/>
                S. Morais<lb/>
                Secretary of the B. H. M<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>SIMON EZEKIEL&#44; Secretary.<lb/>
                1225 North Tenth Street&#44;<lb/>
                Philadelphia.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr M Elkin<lb/>
                871 Marshall St<lb/>
                City<lb/></p>
        </body>
